definition.value: To refer to a person using terms that express the wrong gender, either accidentally or deliberately; for example by calling a woman "son", a boy "she", or an agender individual "he" or "she" instead of "they" (or whatever other pronouns they prefer).
Gender attribution which makes any of a number of assumptions about what does and doesn't line up with one's expectations for or about a particular gender.

A specific form of misgendering in which an individual has their gender ignored or voided, usually in a dehumanizing way, such as referring to a trans woman who uses she/her pronouns with pronouns such as it and singular they.
To misgender someone with the explicit intent to do so, usually as a purposeful expression of transphobia.
To misgender someone without necessarily the explicit intent to do so, usually as the result of an accident.
When unintentionally misgendering occurs, it is usually polite to quickly correct oneself and continue on, rather than to dwell on the accident.
Devices used during sexual activities, practices, or acts in order to reduce the possibility of transmission of sexually-transmitted infections.
Body piercing done for the purpose of enjoying the experience rather than producing a permanent body decoration.
Body piercing done for the purpose of the eroticism of the experience rather than producing a permanent body decoration.
A death in which the cause or manner of death could not be officially determined, or the individual's identity could not be determined.
For deaths in which a cause, manner, and identity are known, but has supposedly involved some conspiracy which may cast doubt on those conclusions, use "death conspiracy theory".

A case of death where the manner is known (murder), but the cause, the identity of the victim, or the location of the victim's remains are unknown or unconfirmed. Additionally, cases of murder wherein legal processes have stalled or remain incomplete because of these aforementioned reasons, or any other reason.
Deaths of individuals who are LGBTQIA+.
Murders of LGBTQIA+ persons; murder in which people who are LGBTQIA+ are the primary victims.
A set of English-language pronouns, usually indicated for use for an individual.
A pronoun set composed of they, them, their, theirs, and themself.
A pronoun set composed of they, them, their, theirs, and themselves.
A set of German-language pronouns, usually indicated for use for an individual.
An English-language gender-neutral pronoun that was invented recently or it otherwise considered a neologism.

A gender-neutral pronoun that was invented recently or it otherwise considered a neologism, that is not necessarily tied to an individual language of use, or is otherwise part of a class of such pronouns which are not tied to a singular language.
A set of Spanish-language pronouns, usually indicated for use for an individual.

A form of the English language spoken in the United Kingdom.

A West Germanic language spoken by about 25 million people as a first language and 5 million people as a second language, constituting most of the population of the Netherlands (where it is the only official language countrywide) and about 60% of the population of Belgium (as one of three official languages).

A Low Franconian dialect cluster of the Dutch language. Flemish is native to Flanders, a historical region in northern Belgium; it is spoken by Flemings, the dominant ethnic group of the region. Outside of Flanders, it is also spoken to some extent in French Flanders and the Dutch Zeelandic Flanders.

An estimation process used to arrive at a group opinion or decision by surveying a panel of experts. These experts respond to several rounds of questionnaires, and the responses are aggregated, anonymized, and shared with the group after each round. The experts are encouraged to revise their answers, considering the replies of other members of their panel, and converge toward a theoretical "best" answer.
A pronoun set composed of ae, aer, aers, and aerself.
Any of various pronoun sets including co and coself.
A pronoun set composed of cy, cyb, cyber, cybers, and cyberself.
